{#-
  reflect.j2 — Reflection prompt template for OpenComputer Evolution.

  Design choices (from design.md §6 and §7):
  - "Be CONSERVATIVE" framing: the reward function is rule-based + LLM-judge is post-v1.1;
    we must not ask the LLM to be optimistic — noop is the safe default.
  - JSON-only output: simplifies B2.3 parsing (no markdown fence stripping needed).
  - evidence_refs cross-check: enables the synthesizer to validate Insights against the
    actual trajectory store before acting.
  - Payload schema documented inline: the LLM has everything it needs in one prompt;
    no chained calls required.

  Whitespace notes: loader sets trim_blocks=True and lstrip_blocks=True.
  Event lines end with a variable tag {{ ... }} (not a block tag) so trim_blocks does
  not consume the trailing newline — metadata is rendered via ternary expression
  rather than {% if %}...{% endif %} for this reason.
-#}
# OpenComputer Evolution — Reflection Pass

You are analyzing recent agent-session trajectories to identify behavioral
patterns worth capturing as new skills or prompt edits. Be CONSERVATIVE:
propose only high-confidence, repeatable patterns. When in doubt, return
action_type "noop".

## Trajectories ({{ records|length }} total, model: {{ model_hint }})

{% for r in records %}
### Trajectory #{{ loop.index }} — session {{ r.session_id }}
- Duration: {{ ((r.ended_at or now) - r.started_at) | round(1) }}s
- Completion: {{ "✓" if r.completion_flag else "✗" }}
- Events: {{ r.events|length }}

{% if r.events %}
Tool sequence:
{% for ev in r.events %}- [{{ ev.action_type }}]{% if ev.tool_name %} {{ ev.tool_name }}{% endif %} → {{ ev.outcome }}{% if ev.metadata.get("error_class") %}  ⚠️ {{ ev.metadata["error_class"] }}: {{ ev.metadata.get("error_message_preview") or "" }}{% endif %}{{ " " + ev.metadata|tojson if ev.metadata else "" }}
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
(no events recorded)
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
## What to return

Return a JSON list of Insight objects. Each Insight is:

  {
    "observation": "<one-sentence pattern description>",
    "evidence_refs": [<trajectory ids — ints from the records above>],
    "action_type": "create_skill" | "edit_prompt" | "noop",
    "payload": { ... action-specific fields ... },
    "confidence": <0.0 to 1.0>
  }

If action_type == "create_skill":
  payload = {
    "slug": "<kebab-case-slug>",
    "name": "<human-readable name>",
    "description": "<one-line summary of when to use>",
    "body": "<markdown body of the skill, 50-300 words>"
  }

If action_type == "edit_prompt":
  payload = {
    "target": "system" | "tool_spec",
    "diff_hint": "<natural-language description of the edit; do NOT write a unified diff>"
  }

If action_type == "noop":
  payload = {"reason": "<why this batch yielded no actionable insight>"}

CRITICAL constraints:
- Return ONLY a JSON array (no surrounding markdown fences, no preamble)
- Every evidence_ref MUST appear in the trajectories above
- confidence < 0.5 means the Insight will be filtered; only return high-confidence findings
- Privacy: do not echo raw prompt text in observations or payloads (you didn't see any prompts — only tool sequences)

## Notes

- The most recent trajectory ended {{ ((now - (records[-1].ended_at or now)) / 60) | round(1) if records else 0 }} minutes ago.
- Trajectories with completion_flag=✗ may indicate workflow gaps worth a skill.
- Repeated tool patterns across multiple trajectories are stronger signals than single-session quirks.
